<paragraph blockId="19.[136,1452,158,725]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis box="[189,253,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[274,519,626,652]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis box="[274,519,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Roussoella siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. Q. Dai, J. K. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2014" box="[757,942,626,652]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="neopustulans">
<emphasis box="[757,942,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">R. neopustulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it is hard to separate them based on morphological characters. However they are phylogenetically distinct from each other in all the phylogenetic reconstructions. Therefore, we describe this fungus as a new species.
</paragraph>
